    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="221"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/1747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 23, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>94. Your 78, November 23, 2 p.m. <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> report is
                    complete misinterpretation of certain provisions of debt bill, translation of
                    which is given in my telegram 96, November 23, 10 p.m.<note n="50"
                        xml:id="d221fn50">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note> Bill does not affect payment of duties.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
